project: You made three mistakes and lost this game.

A sudoku puzzle begins with a grid in which some of the numbers are already in place. 
A puzzle is completed when each number from 1 to 9 appears only once in each of the 9 [color=#d8840e]rows[/color], [color=#d80e0e]columns[/color], and [color=#12ba3c]blocks[/color]. Study the grid to find the numbers that might fit into each cell.
